body:
### Version

Yosys 0.24+10 (git sha1 3ebc50dee, gcc 9.3.0-22 -fPIC -Os)

### On which OS did this happen?

Linux

### Reproduction Steps

While processing a single element of `typedef struct packed` by a `$bits` function, it returns size of a whole structure.
Example design:
```verilog
module top(output int o);

	typedef struct packed {
		logic [1:0][15:0] v_2x16;
		logic [1:0] 	  v_2bit;
	} struct_2el;

	struct_2el array;

	assign o = $bits(array.v_2x16[0]);
endmodule
```
Executed commands:
```bash
$ yosys
yosys> read_verilog -sv -dump_vlog2 top.sv
```

It should return a size of single `[15:0]` element of `v_2x16`.

### Expected Behavior

Yosys should inffer a value equal to a size of an expression passed to `$bits`:
```verilog
assign o = 16;
```

### Actual Behavior

Yosys inffers a value equal to the size of a whole structure:
```verilog
assign o = 34;
```

